The fix is in commit 8c94821. The root cause was that robot convert dropped 
  the owl:imports for mondo_import.owl from the ontology header when I ran    
  normalization using a dummy empty imports/mondo_import.owl file. This caused
  27 MONDO terms to appear as "dangling" in the built ontology since their    
  definitions weren't loaded. Restoring the single missing import statement   
  fixes the CI failure.

